<div id="pf8" class="pf w2 h18" data-page-no="8"><div class="pc pc8 w2 h18"><img class="bi x0 y0 w3 h19" alt="" src="bg8.png"/><div class="t m102 x5c h21 ye1 ff5 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">LESSON 1 </div><div class="t m103 x5f h22 ye2 ff2 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">*December 27â€”January 2 </div><div class="t m104 x56 h23 ye3 ff1 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">The Unique Purpose </div><div class="t m105 x56 h23 ye4 ff2 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">of </div><div class="t m106 x60 h24 ye5 ff5 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">John&apos;s Gospel </div><div class="t m107 x56 h9 y6d ff5 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">SABBATH AFTERNOON </div><div class="t m108 x61 h25 ye6 ff3 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Read for This Week&apos;s Study: </div><div class="t m19 x41 h3 ye7 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"> Luke 1:1-4, John 15:1-8, </div><div class="t m109 x56 h3 ye8 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">17:20, 20:24-31, 21:20-25. </div><div class="t m10a x61 h25 ye9 ff3 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Memory Text: </div><div class="t m10b x24 h9 yea ff5 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"> &quot;Then Jesus told him, &apos;Because you have seen </div><div class="t m10c x56 h9 yeb ff5 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">me, you have believed; blessed are those who have not seen and yet </div><div class="t m69 x56 h9 yec ff5 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">have believed&apos; &quot; </div><div class="t m10d x62 h3 yed ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(John 20:29, NIV). </div><div class="t m10e x61 h25 yee ff3 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Key Thought: </div><div class="t m10f x62 h9 y48 ff5 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"> The Gospel of John tells us that the absence of </div><div class="t m110 x63 h9 yef ff5 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">physical contact with Jesus is no disadvantage to those seeking a </div><div class="t m111 x63 h9 yf0 ff5 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">relationship with Him today. Jesus&apos; word is as powerful as His </div><div class="t m39 x63 h9 yf1 ff5 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">touch. </div><div class="t m112 x63 h26 yf2 ff5 fs17 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">H</div><div class="t m42 x5d h3 yf3 ff1 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">ave you ever wished you could have known Jesus in the flesh, </div><div class="t m113 x5d h3 yf4 ff1 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">as His disciples did? Have you ever wished He lived at your </div><div class="t m114 x5d h3 yf5 ff1 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">house? Wouldn&apos;t it be great to take your problems directly to </div><div class="t m115 x63 h3 y4e ff1 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Him, face to face? To go to Him and share what&apos;s on your heart and </div><div class="t m112 x63 h3 yf6 ff1 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">then see Him go to His knees and pray earnestly to His Father for you? </div><div class="t m116 x63 h3 y91 ff1 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Wouldn&apos;t it be easier to have a relationship with Jesus if He lived, </div><div class="t m117 x63 h3 yf7 ff1 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">breathed, walked, and talked at your house? </div><div class="t m118 x1a h3 yf8 ff1 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">But that privilege has not been ours. Yet, the good news is that the </div><div class="t m119 x63 h3 yf9 ff1 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Gospel of John helps assure us that we don&apos;t need physical contact with </div><div class="t m11a x63 h3 yfa ff1 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Jesus in order to have a relationship with Him. We don&apos;t need physical </div><div class="t m11b x63 h3 yfb ff1 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">contact to obtain all the blessings He is willing and able to give. John </div><div class="t m11c x63 h3 yfc ff1 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">even recalls Jesus telling His disciples &quot; &apos;It is for your good that I am </div><div class="t m11d x63 h3 yfd ff1 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">going away&apos; &quot; </div><div class="t m11e x64 h3 yfd ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(John 16:7, NIV). </div><div class="t m11f x59 h3 yfd ff1 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Through the presence of the Spirit, the </div><div class="t m120 x63 h3 yfe ff1 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">work of Jesus is enhanced by His absence </div><div class="t m121 x39 h3 yfe ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(John 14:12). </div><div class="t m122 x1a h3 yff ff1 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">This week we take our first look at this good news. </div><div class="t m84 x61 h3 yc1 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">*Study this week&apos;s lesson to prepare for Sabbath, January 3. </div><div class="t mf0 x65 h3 y100 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">6 </div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000000,1.000000,0.000000,0.000000]}'></div></div>
